        <content>
          <p>TITLE XXIII--OCCUPANCY AND POSSESSION
CHAPTER 1--OCCUPANCY
Art. 3412.  Occupancy
Occupancy is the taking of possession of a corporeal movable that does not belong to anyone.  The occupant acquires ownership the moment he takes possession.</p>
        </content>
